00:30:05,563 --> 00:30:07,603
I've heard of it.

249
00:30:10,027 --> 00:30:14,985
I like a man who's been around.
I grew up there when Dad was playing.

250
00:30:15,115 --> 00:30:18,900
My mom's still there.
She's remarried to some jerk.

251
00:30:19,036 --> 00:30:21,492
Pardon me - rich jerk.

252
00:30:22,707 --> 00:30:25,163
I've only been up here a couple of years.

253
00:30:25,293 --> 00:30:29,125
You oughta spend a Saturday night
in Stanton sometime.

254
00:30:29,255 --> 00:30:31,747
No, thank you.

255
00:30:31,883 --> 00:30:34,457
It's not like Murray doesn't try.

256
00:30:34,595 --> 00:30:39,304
He made me stick boy for the team, then
he wouldn't let me into the locker room.

257
00:30:39,433 --> 00:30:41,758
I can't imagine why not.

258
00:30:41,894 --> 00:30:44,350
Now he's got me on the Zamboni.

259
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:49,523
My big goal in life is to do the ice
at Madison Square Garden.

260
00:30:50,612 --> 00:30:52,854
At least you have a reason to be here.

261
00:30:52,989 --> 00:30:55,315
Where else could I get
beaten up every day,

262
00:30:55,450 --> 00:31:00,908
treated like shit by a bunch of prima
donna Canadians, get my nuts shaved...

263
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:03,911
Don't worry.
It grows back.

264
00:31:05,836 --> 00:31:08,921
At least you still have your own teeth.

265
00:31:12,719 --> 00:31:14,130
Or don't you?

266
00:31:16,056 --> 00:31:18,629
Yep, still mine.

267
00:31:25,316 --> 00:31:30,441
Look... I think you're real nice
and got a cute ass,

268
00:31:33,491 --> 00:31:39,281
but I don't think it's a good idea
if we see each other. OK?

269
00:31:45,003 --> 00:31:47,210
Thanks for the book.

270
00:31:48,799 --> 00:31:50,839
Sure.

271
00:31:55,848 --> 00:31:59,134
