344
00:40:34,781 --> 00:40:38,648
It's either this or Slumber Party Massacre.
Come on.

345
00:40:38,785 --> 00:40:43,744
Don't worry. I'll catch you if you fall.
Just hold onto the side and you'll be fine.

346
00:40:43,874 --> 00:40:45,914
There we go.

347
00:40:48,838 --> 00:40:51,126
There you go.
Looking better.

348
00:40:51,257 --> 00:40:53,297
Good. Keep going.

349
00:40:56,346 --> 00:40:59,550
- You're real coordinated.
- I'll play for New York someday.

350
00:40:59,683 --> 00:41:03,383
I think you oughta learn how to skate first.

351
00:41:05,939 --> 00:41:08,513
You two all right?

352
00:41:08,651 --> 00:41:11,486
Yeah, we're just fine.
It's his first time.

353
00:41:11,613 --> 00:41:16,073
You better stay alongside of the boards
or you're gonna get run over.

354
00:41:16,576 --> 00:41:18,616
OK.

355
00:41:20,622 --> 00:41:22,662
Come on.

356
00:41:28,839 --> 00:41:31,674
- (Dean) So, you can skate.
- (guard) Damn kids.

357
00:41:31,801 --> 00:41:34,374
Too bad for you, cos you're it.

358
00:41:49,528 --> 00:41:51,568
Hey, lady, slow down!

359
00:41:52,824 --> 00:41:54,899
(blows whistle)

360
00:41:58,997 --> 00:42:00,159
Gotcha!

361
00:42:29,196 --> 00:42:31,236
(Murray singing)

362
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:37,200
In here.

363
00:42:47,048 --> 00:42:48,163
Shit.

364
00:42:54,890 --> 00:42:57,049
Great voice.

365
00:42:57,185 --> 00:42:59,223
Closet crooner.

366
00:43:02,398 --> 00:43:04,936
"Mad Dog" Murray Chadwick.

367
00:43:07,904 --> 00:43:09,447
Look.

368
00:43:09,573 --> 00:43:12,194
Second row.

369
00:43:12,325 --> 00:43:15,280
I used to go to all the games.

370
00:43:15,412 --> 00:43:18,781
Right next to the penalty box
so you could be near your old man.

371
00:43:18,916 --> 00:43:20,992
He never lost a fight, did he?

372
00:43:21,127 --> 00:43:28,126
He wasn't just some goon. I was there
when he got a goal in an all-star game.

373
00:43:33,640 --> 00:43:37,223
All I remember is my dad
racing up the ice with the puck,

374
00:43:37,352 --> 00:43:42,394
got up to the blue line, cut across
the middle and then blasted it on the fly.

375
00:43:43,484 --> 00:43:46,854
Upper left-hand corner.
Goalie never moved.

376
00:43:46,988 --> 00:43:50,191
I thought you didn't follow hockey.
Or hockey players.

377
00:44:06,425 --> 00:44:08,465
What?

378
00:44:12,682 --> 00:44:15,683
Dean, what happens
if you don't make the pros?

379
00:44:15,810 --> 00:44:17,850
I'll make the pros.

380
00:44:17,979 --> 00:44:20,019
What if you don't?

381
00:44:22,651 --> 00:44:26,316
Ever since I was six years old,
I've been faster than anyone.

382
00:44:26,446 --> 00:44:31,821
Even kids three and four years older
than I was, they could never catch me.

383
00:44:31,953 --> 00:44:36,117
They used to try and beat the shit
out of me instead.

384
00:44:38,085 --> 00:44:40,160
We got this big pond on our farm.

385
00:44:40,295 --> 00:44:45,835
As soon as it would freeze over, me and
my brother Kelly would put on our skates.

386
00:44:45,968 --> 00:44:48,673
We'd stay out there all day long.

387
00:44:49,931 --> 00:44:55,221
It'd be dark by the time we got home. We
had to sit by the fire to thaw out our feet.

388
00:44:55,353 --> 00:44:58,556
My mom used to think we were crazy.

389
00:44:58,690 --> 00:45:01,857
I remember never wanting to come in
when I was young.

390
00:45:01,985 --> 00:45:06,029
When you were young.
How old do you think you are?

391
00:45:06,156 --> 00:45:11,862
17. If I don't sign a pro contract
in the next couple of years, I'm through.

392
00:45:11,996 --> 00:45:18,283
It's just the way it works. And I don't
wanna work in a goddamn mill or farm.

393
00:45:23,258 --> 00:45:26,093
What does your mother
think about all this?

394
00:45:26,219 --> 00:45:32,305
She left my dad and us about four years
ago. She doesn't know what's going on.

395
00:45:32,434 --> 00:45:33,893
I'm sorry.

396
00:45:36,731 --> 00:45:39,222
I guess she got tired of the farm too.

397
00:45:39,359 --> 00:45:45,563
My brother and I got used to her being
gone, but I don't think my old man has.

398
00:45:55,084 --> 00:45:57,123
- Still hurt?
- No.

399
00:46:05,220 --> 00:46:07,758
Maybe I will.

400
00:46:07,889 --> 00:46:09,928
Will what?

401
00:46:11,851 --> 00:46:14,722
Start following hockey again.

402
00:46:20,403 --> 00:46:22,442
(giggling)

403
00:46:29,704 --> 00:46:32,160
- Good book?
- Great writer.

404
00:46:43,469 --> 00:46:46,423
- It's a nice room.
- It's not bad.

405
00:46:46,555 --> 00:46:48,263
(bed springs creak)

406
00:46:48,391 --> 00:46:53,349
- Bed's a little creaky.
- Tell me about it. I use it every night.

407
00:46:53,480 --> 00:46:55,520
To sleep on.

408
00:46:56,483 --> 00:46:58,523
Of course.

409
00:48:32,669 --> 00:48:34,709
(kettle whistles)

410
00:48:36,507 --> 00:48:40,636
("Get Ready" by Diana Ross
and the Supremes on radio)

411
00:49:03,787 --> 00:49:06,324
(hums along to radio)

412
00:50:08,731 --> 00:50:10,973
No, no! Don't!

413
00:50:28,294 --> 00:50:30,334
(Jessie) Stop it!

414
00:50:45,396 --> 00:50:47,436
Room service?

415
00:50:55,490 --> 00:50:56,865
(bell rings)

416
00:50:57,617 --> 00:50:59,657
God, he's good.

417
00:51:02,831 --> 00:51:05,286
